<li id="cite_note-50"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-50">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">As the Arabs of the Ḥejāz had used the drahms of the Sasanian-style, the only silver coinage in the world at that time, it was natural for them to leave many of the Sasanian mints in operation, striking coins like those of the emperors in every detail except for the addition of brief Arabic inscriptions like besmellāh in the margins.<a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/coins-and-coinage-">https://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/coins-and-coinage-</a></span>
